; Regression test for issue #1033:
; The print command should preserve {{total}} lot-price notation rather than
; converting it to {per-unit} notation.  For example, -100 AAA {{90.00 GBP}}
; means the total cost for the lot is 90.00 GBP.  The old code divided by the
; quantity and printed {0.90 GBP}, which changes the user's notation and
; produces repeating decimals for non-divisible cases.
;
; NOTE: The second lot (bought via @@, not {{}}) prints as {1.00 GBP}
; (per-unit) because the input used @@ total-price syntax, not {{}}
; lot-price notation.  Only explicit {{}} notation is preserved.

2011-11-03 * Buy AAA
    Assets:Investments                  100 AAA @@ 100.00 GBP
    Assets:Cash

2011-12-06 * Sell
    Assets:Investments                                      400.00 GBP
    Assets:Investments    -100 AAA {{ 90.00 GBP}} [2010-06-10] @  2 GBP
    Assets:Investments    -100 AAA {{100.00 GBP}} [2011-11-03] @  2 GBP
    Income:Capital gains                                   -210.00 GBP

test print
2011/11/03 * Buy AAA
    Assets:Investments                       100 AAA @@ 100.00 GBP
    Assets:Cash

2011/12/06 * Sell
    Assets:Investments                    400.00 GBP
    Assets:Investments                  -100 AAA {{90.00 GBP}} [2010/06/10] @ 2.00 GBP
    Assets:Investments                  -100 AAA {1.00 GBP} [2011/11/03] @ 2.00 GBP
    Income:Capital gains                 -210.00 GBP
end test
